f^+ - f^-
g_1(\omega)
g_2(\omega)
f^+
f^-
 \int_{-\infty}^\infty f'(u) du = \int_{-\infty}^\infty du \int_0^\infty d\omega~ \omega \left( g_1(\omega)e^{-i \omega u} - g_2(\omega)e^{i \omega u} \right) = \frac{1}{2} \lim_{\omega \to 0} \left[ \omega \left( g_1(\omega)  - g_2(\omega) \right) \right] 
 f^+ - f^- = \frac{1}{2} \lim_{\omega \to 0} \left[ \omega \left( g_1(\omega)  - g_2(\omega) \right) \right] 
 \int_{-\infty}^\infty du~f(u) = \frac{i}{2} \lim_{\omega \to 0}  \left[ g_1(\omega)  + g_2(\omega) \right] 
